@Comment:	dinner is with Chi , MOT , and Mot's parents (who live upstairs I think) and occurs on the same day as the home visit; they talk about the study for awhile , which involves discussion of Rafael's name and of how the study will continue until we run out of funds (Chi asks what do you mean by funds?); Chi offers to make a donation so the study can continue; they discuss the logistics for tomorrow's karate lesson and a visit to a Christmas Bazaar; Chi gets an allowance; Chi says of extra food <can you please save that for another day>; Chi burps and GRM calls him a piglet , after which Chi repeats over and over <I know you are but what am I>; the topics and the general conversation are quite child-centered; there's something having to do with tying Chi but he is enthusiastic about it , whatever it is; MT is about 27 minutes long
